## Implementation Details

The SpeedInsights component was added to the main entry point (`main.tsx`) following the official Vercel documentation for React applications. The component is positioned at the root level of the application, wrapped within the existing provider hierarchy (ThemeProvider > AuthProvider) to ensure proper tracking across all routes.

The implementation follows the pattern:
```tsx
import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';

// Inside ReactDOM.createRoot:
<AuthProvider>
  <RouterProvider router={router} />
  <SpeedInsights />
</AuthProvider>
```

This placement ensures that Speed Insights will:
- Track performance metrics across all routes handled by react-router-dom
- Work within the authentication context
- Be initialized once when the application starts

